  "description": "Legume/bean family — ~770 genera, ~19,500 species (third-largest angiosperm family). Diagnostic pod (legume) fruit, nitrogen-fixing symbiosis with Rhizobium. Three subfamilies with distinct flower morphology. Economically dominant family for protein crops and nitrogen cycling.",
